        prayer: "God, I'm angry. I've been saying I'm fine. I've been singing the songs. I've been giving the right answers. But I'm not fine. I'm angry about things I don't understand. I don't understand why You allowed it. I don't understand why You didn't answer. I don't understand why it still hurts. And pretending not to be angry isn't working anymore. So here I am. Angry. Confused. Still here. I don't need You to fix it right now. I just need You to not leave while I say all of this. Thank You for being big enough to hold my anger. Amen.",
        declaration: "My anger does not disqualify me from God's presence. Honesty is not disrespect—it is intimacy. God is big enough to handle my real emotions. Today, I stop pretending and start telling the truth."
